for the headset. The device will also stop getting bug fixes and security patches in August.\n\n“As we continue developing Beat Saber, our goal is to raise the bar of what’s possible,” the support page reads. “To focus our efforts in the right direction, we will no longer support Meta Quest 1 devices.”\n\nBeat Saber isn’t the only game limiting functionality on the Quest 1. Population: One stopped letting Quest 1 players launch or play the game in 2022, while Meta Horizon Home axed social features for the headset last March. Sadly, we’ll likely see more games end support for the headset as the deadline for the Quest 1’s final security and bug fix approaches.\n"}],"package":null,"url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/6/24150119/beat-saber-quest-1-end-online-support-multiplayer","commentsClosed":false,"railComponents":[{"__typename":"EntryRailNewsletter","entryRailNewsletter":{"name":"Verge Deals","slug":"deals"}}],"dek":{"plaintext":"The game will also stop receiving updates and customer support."},"leadImage":{"defaultImageUrl":"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HvgeuuSqOWoSNLgALx2yN6brKa0=/0x0:1920x1080/1200x628/filters:focal(960x540:961x541)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25435341/beat_saber_screenshot.jpg","asset":{"title":"A screenshot from Beat Saber","contentType":"image/jpeg"}},"seoDescription":{"plaintext":"Beat Saber is ending multiplayer support for users with a Quest 1 headset in November 2024. The change will also stop updates and customer support."},"socialDescription":{"plaintext":"Support ends in November."},"socialImage":null,"shouldUseHTMLNoindex":false,"shouldUseHTMLNofollow":false,"password":null,"additionalContributors":null,"_id":23914160,"leadComponent":{"__typename":"EntryLeadImage","standard":{"hideCredit":false,"asset":{"title":"A screenshot from Beat Saber"},"caption":null,"credit":{"html":"Image: Beat Games"},"variantUrl":"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/uc8hbLrQ1h44zTJjfevoJahNVSo=/0x0:1920x1080/2000x1333/filters:focal(960x540:96